    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-28T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="752"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.AD1/362a: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Certain
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular Officers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="36" xml:id="d752fn36">Sent to the diplomatic and consular officers in
                        countries invited to the Food and Agriculture Conference, except the Soviet
                        Union, the Dominican Republic, Poland, Belgium, and Norway. Similar
                        instructions were sent April 28, 1943, 10 p.m., to the Ambassadors in the
                        Soviet Union (No. 264), and the United Kingdom for Biddle (Polish Series No.
                        9, Belgian Series No. 8, and Norwegian Series No. 1).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-28T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 28, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference circular telegram April 13, noon, and previous concerning United
                    Nations Food Conference. Please inform the government to which you are
                    accredited that the definitive agenda which has been agreed upon following
                    consultation with the governments invited ta participate in the Conference
                    differs from the proposed agenda only in paragraph II. A. which has now been
                    revised to read as follows: “Measures for direction of production toward
                    commodities, the supply of which should be increased.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
